WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.920
Hello, my name is David.
Hola mi nombre es David.

00:00:02.920 --> 00:00:09.860
Is my name David? [YES/NO], it is.

00:00:09.860 --> 00:00:13.500
I am thirty-two years old.
Tengo treinta y dos años de edad.

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:20.870
Am I thirty-two years old? [YES/NO], I am.

00:00:20.870 --> 00:00:25.290
I live in Colombia.
Vivo en Colombia.

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:31.400
Do I live in the United States? [YES/NO], I don’t.

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:34.879
I am from the United States.
Soy de Estados Unidos.

00:00:34.879 --> 00:00:42.280
Am I from the United States? [YES/NO], I am.

00:00:42.280 --> 00:00:45.280
I am married.
Estoy casado.

00:00:45.280 --> 00:00:50.980
Am I single? [YES/NO], I’m not.

00:00:50.980 --> 00:00:55.520
My wife and I have three children.
Mi esposa y yo tenemos tres hijos.

00:00:55.520 --> 00:01:02.500
Do I have three children? [YES/NO], I do.

00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:07.080
I have two sons and one daughter.
Tengo dos hijos y una hija.

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:13.120
Do I have three sons? [YES/NO], I don’t.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:17.912
Their names are John, Kevin, and Ann.
Sus nombres son John, Kevin y Ann.

00:01:17.912 --> 00:01:25.441
Is my daughter’s name Ann? [YES/NO], it is.

00:01:25.441 --> 00:01:28.579
We also have a dog.
También tenemos un perro.

00:01:28.579 --> 00:01:33.684
Do I have a cat? [YES/NO], I don’t.

00:01:33.684 --> 00:01:37.930
The dog’s name is Buster.
El nombre del perro es Buster.

00:01:37.930 --> 00:01:44.703
Is my dog’s name Fido? [YES/NO], it isn’t.

00:01:44.703 --> 00:01:47.839
I work as a postman.
Soy cartero.

00:01:47.839 --> 00:01:53.126
Do I have a job? [YES/NO], I do.

00:01:53.126 --> 00:01:57.312
I deliver the mail each day.
Entrego el correo todos los días.

00:01:57.312 --> 00:02:03.114
Do I deliver the mail? [YES/NO], I do.

00:02:03.114 --> 00:02:08.598
I like to eat American food.
Me gusta comer comida americana.

00:02:08.598 --> 00:02:14.701
Do I like to eat Italian food? [YES/NO], I don’t.

00:02:14.701 --> 00:02:18.546
Hot dogs are delicious.
Los perros calientes son deliciosos.

00:02:18.546 --> 00:02:24.235
Do I think hot dogs are delicious? [YES/NO], I do.

00:02:24.235 --> 00:02:27.713
I also like to cook.
También me gusta cocinar.

00:02:27.713 --> 00:02:33.467
Is cooking something I like to do? [YES/NO], it is.

00:02:33.467 --> 00:02:38.549
Cakes are my favorite food to bake.
Los pasteles son mi comida favorita para hornear.

00:02:38.549 --> 00:02:43.453
Can I bake a cake? [YES/NO], I can.

00:02:43.453 --> 00:02:48.582
Cakes are also my favorite food to eat.
Los pasteles también son mi comida favorita para comer.

00:02:48.582 --> 00:02:55.676
Are donuts my favorite food to eat? [YES/NO], they aren’t.

00:02:55.676 --> 00:02:59.486
I also enjoy exercising.
También disfruto hacer ejercicio.

00:02:59.486 --> 00:03:05.934
Do I enjoy exercising? [YES/NO], I do.

00:03:05.934 --> 00:03:09.727
I like to run and hike.
Me gusta correr y hacer senderismo.

00:03:09.727 --> 00:03:17.318
Do I like to swim? [YES/NO], I don’t.

00:03:17.318 --> 00:03:22.511
After eating hot dogs and cakes, I need to exercise.
Después de comer perros calientes y pasteles, necesito hacer ejercicio.

00:03:22.511 --> 00:03:31.261
After eating cake, do I need to sleep? [YES/NO], I don’t.
